sentences: Steve Wright (1950 – January 16, 2017) was an American bass guitarist best known for his work with The Greg Kihn Band.
After changing their name to Hades Blues Works (later, Hades), they expanded into a quartet with Craig Ferreira in 1970 (he left in 1971).

Wright died of a heart attack at UC Davis Hospital in Sacramento, California, in the early hours of January 16, 2017.
